"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-sport-olympics-sir-matthew-pinsent-rages-bbc-olympics-boxing-saga\", \"text\": \"Sir Matthew Pinsent has raged at the International Olympic Committee after Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting won gold in Paris this summer  BBC  ByJack Otway,  Published: 12/08/2024  The Team GB hero has opened up after Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting won gold in Paris  Sir Matthew Pinsent has raged at the International Olympic Committee after Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting won gold in Paris this summer.  Both boxers had previously failed gender eligibility tests at the World Boxing Championships last year.  The tests are confidential but the International Boxing Association, which has been discredited, have alleged that both fighters are 'biologically male'.Khelif won gold by beating China's Yang Liu on Friday.Sir Matthew Pinsent has raged at the International Olympic Committee after Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting won gold in Paris this summer|BBCAnd Lin wrote her name into Olympic folklore with victory over Poland's Julia Szeremeta on Saturday.Pinsent, speaking live on the BBC, has now blasted the IOC.He says they can not have 'equity and inclusion' and says the controversy has been one of their own making.\\\"While Paris has been a huge success there have been some very unfortunate headlines about boxing and the IOC, in a sense, asked for that,\\\" he said.JUST IN:BBC commentator triggers backlash as England joke backfires at Paris Olympics closing ceremony\\\"Because they stepped in and said 'we do not like the way boxing is being run, we are going to make the rules for the Olympics and the inclusion of athletes boxing here' and that has basically exploded on them.\\\"It's been really unfortunate.\\\"It has been totally of their own creation because they can not have both equity and inclusion.\\\"It's so weird they allowed it to happen.READ MORE:Wayne Rooney called 'the worst manager ever' as Plymouth boss suffers nightmare start to new job\\\"They can not organise an event and say 'on the one hand we are just organising the Olympics'. And then the other diving into a sport and saying 'we are also going to rewrite the rulebook for Paris.'\\\"That has been really unpleasant and unfortunate.\\\"Both Khelif and Lin have bristled at suggestions that they are 'biologically male'.Khelif haseven filed an official complaint with Paris prosecutorsas she looks to combat the abuse she's received online.LATEST SPORTS NEWS:Luke Littler makes brutal admission after crushing 8-1 defeat to Gerwyn Price at Australian Darts MastersMan Utd duo left furious with Andre Onana during Community Shield defeat to Man CityBBC Olympics fans fume at broadcaster over sound blunder during closing ceremony: 'Absolute mess!'Imane Khelif won gold at the Paris Olympics on Friday with the Algerian triumphing despite scrutiny over her gender|PAFans on X have responded to Pinsent's rant.And many are in agreement with the 53-year-old, who won four medals throughout his career in rowing.\\\"Wow are the BBC turning over a new leaf, or will Matthew get his wrist slapped? said one user.Lin Yu-Ting followed in the footsteps of Imane Khelif by also winning gold at the Paris Olympics|PAAnother said: \\\"He's completely correct.\\\"A third stated: \\\"It's the truth. People should try speaking this way more often.\\\"And a fourth said: \\\"Good for him.\\\"  The tests are confidential but the International Boxing Association, which has been discredited, have alleged that both fighters are 'biologically male'.  Khelif won gold by beating China's Yang Liu on Friday.  Sir Matthew Pinsent has raged at the International Olympic Committee after Imane Khelif and Lin Yu-Ting won gold in Paris this summer  BBC  And Lin wrote her name into Olympic folklore with victory over Poland's Julia Szeremeta on Saturday.  Pinsent, speaking live on the BBC, has now blasted the IOC.  He says they can not have 'equity and inclusion' and says the controversy has been one of their own making.  \\\"While Paris has been a huge success there have been some very unfortunate headlines about boxing and the IOC, in a sense, asked for that,\\\" he said.  JUST IN:BBC commentator triggers backlash as England joke backfires at Paris Olympics closing ceremony  \\\"Because they stepped in and said 'we do not like the way boxing is being run, we are going to make the rules for the Olympics and the inclusion of athletes boxing here' and that has basically exploded on them.  \\\"It's been really unfortunate.  \\\"It has been totally of their own creation because they can not have both equity and inclusion.  \\\"It's so weird they allowed it to happen.  READ MORE:Wayne Rooney called 'the worst manager ever' as Plymouth boss suffers nightmare start to new job  \\\"They can not organise an event and say 'on the one hand we are just organising the Olympics'. And then the other diving into a sport and saying 'we are also going to rewrite the rulebook for Paris.'  \\\"That has been really unpleasant and unfortunate.\\\"  Both Khelif and Lin have bristled at suggestions that they are 'biologically male'.  Khelif haseven filed an official complaint with Paris prosecutorsas she looks to combat the abuse she's received online.  LATEST SPORTS NEWS:  Imane Khelif won gold at the Paris Olympics on Friday with the Algerian triumphing despite scrutiny over her gender  PA  Fans on X have responded to Pinsent's rant.  And many are in agreement with the 53-year-old, who won four medals throughout his career in rowing.  \\\"Wow are the BBC turning over a new leaf, or will Matthew get his wrist slapped? said one user.  Lin Yu-Ting followed in the footsteps of Imane Khelif by also winning gold at the Paris Olympics  PA  Another said: \\\"He's completely correct.\\\"  A third stated: \\\"It's the truth. People should try speaking this way more often.\\\"  And a fourth said: \\\"Good for him.\\\"  \"}"